Reasoning: The paper discusses a statistical estimation procedure based on machine learning for learning and designing stochastic processes from logical constraints. This involves the use of linear temporal logic formulae to encode qualitative properties of the system. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the use of statistical methods, which suggests the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possibility. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the method to social networks and gene regulation, which suggests the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering) as a possibility.
